race.description: Roger Moylan Memorial Country Boosted Plate (C2)
race.comment: SNATCHREILLY (5) doesn't win out of turn but is as honest as they come. He has good early muster, draws to advantage, and should be in this for a very long way. GELSEY (8) went right on with it second-up at Walcha, putting his CL1 away with authority. He strips fitter again and has more to offer - he'll just need a touch of luck from the wide alley. NATION CHANGING (4) returns. Couldn't get going in his second prep, after going 2/2 in his debut campaign. Has been readied with a Scone trial and reunites with winning hoop in Weir. Can play a major role fresh. KAWATIRI (11) charged home strongly to get off the mark two back at Gunnedah. Less effective last time but is worth keeping in mind.
